<p>Earlier in the day, Bella hinted she could be Australia's next Bachelorette after getting her heart broken during The Bachelor finale.   </p>

<p>Speaking exclusively to Daily Mail Australia on Friday, the Bachelor runner-up confessed she'd love to be cast on the reality show. </p>

<p>'Yeah, I mean, what a way to get your happily ever after!' she said.   </p>

<p>Bella was left shell-shocked during Thursday's Bachelor finale when Locky Gilbert, 31, told both her and love rival Irena Srbinovska he loved them - only to dump her. </p>

<p>Heartbroken: Bella was left shell-shocked during Thursday's Bachelor finale when Locky Gilbert, 31, told both her and love rival Irena Srbinovska he loved them - only to dump her </p>

<p>Dumped: Locky (right) broke down in tears as Bella arrived to face the music, telling her he 'fell in love' the first day he saw her, before coming up with a rather feeble excuse to end things</p>

<p>Happy ending! In the end, Locky chose to pursue a relationship with Irena (left) </p>

<p>He broke down in tears as Bella arrived to face the music, telling her he 'fell in love' the first day he saw her, before coming up with a rather feeble excuse to end things.  </p>

<p>'I know you don't, like, sort of see where your future is at the moment. I think I need just a little bit of certainty,' he said, as Bella looked at him in utter disbelief.</p>

<p>'I just don't know if I can see us working,' he added, to which the brunette replied: 'I just don't get it. Yesterday, you told me you were in love with me.'</p>

<p>Instead, Locky chose to pursue a relationship with nurse Irena Srbinovska.</p>

